### Steps to reproduce
```html
<div id="app">
    <div>Global component</div>
    <global-com/>
    <div>Local components</div>
    <local-com1/>
    <local-com2/>
</div>
```
```javascript
Vue.component("global-com", {
    template: "<p style='color:#F00;'>global</p>"
});
var app = new Vue({
    el: "#app",
    components: {
        "local-com1": {
            template: "<p style='color:#F00;'>local-1</p>"
        },
        "local-com2": {
            template: "<p style='color:#0FF;'>local-2</p>"
        }
    }
});
```
You just need to run the page.

===================

### What is expected?
Global components should be as a backup, Local components not covered, refer to the definition of a global component.

### What is actually happening?
Only <global-com/> a work, If exchange definition (global & local) after the order, only the first local components effectively.

